+
+Read only what is needed to operate:
+1. `AGENTS.md`
+2. `prompts/v2-answer-first/*`
+3. `runtime/answer-first-run/README.md`
+4. the exact named `runtime/answer-first-run/turn-XXX/*` only when the user explicitly says `resume`
+
+Hard isolation rule:
+- For a brand-new answer-first run, the only runtime turn path in scope is the new folder you create under `runtime/answer-first-run/turn-XXX/`.
+- Any file under `runtime/active-run/` is out of scope and must not be opened, cited, or reused.
+- Any old `v2-canon` packet shape is out of scope and must not be reused as a template for this variant.
+- Any folder under `runtime/answer-first-run/archive/` is evidence only and must not be treated as resumable run state.
+
+Live runtime shape:
+- controller = OCR binder + full answer packet + controller-side web search + packet transport + live tutor output + cleanup
+- verifier1 = adversarial falsifier + baseline answer verifier + turn verifier + transcript auditor
+
+Exact child stage bindings:
+- Controller stage:
+  - output family = controller answer packet
+  - expected root fields include:
+    - `exact_visible_text`
+    - `answer_claims`
+    - `solved_answers`
+    - `controller_supporting_sources`
+    - `visible_tutor_cycle`
+- Stage 1 child:
+  - prompt file = `prompts/v2-answer-first/03 VERIFIER1 - adversarial falsifier v2.txt`
+  - mode = `BASELINE_ANSWER_VERIFICATION`
+  - expected output family = verifier/proof packet
+- Stage 2 child:
+  - prompt file = `prompts/v2-answer-first/03 VERIFIER1 - adversarial falsifier v2.txt`
+  - mode = `TURN_CONSISTENCY_CHECK`
+  - expected output family = verifier/proof packet
+
+Wrong-role guard:
+- If a supposed verifier child returns answer-packet root fields such as:
+  - `answer_claims`
+  - `solved_answers`
+  - `controller_supporting_sources`
+  - `visible_tutor_cycle`
+  treat it as `WRONG_ROLE_OUTPUT`.
+- Wrong-role output must not be saved as stage-complete.
+
+Current canonical rules that matter:
+- precedence = runtime contract > role prompt > skill > human-facing wording
+- no interrupt on delay alone
+- source policy = 2 independent directly opened live sources by default for substantive answer claims
+- output layers remain separate
+- canonical fail strings:
+  - EXECUTION FAILED, REQUEST AGAIN OR TRY WITH A BACKUP AGENT
+  - UNVERIFIED - DO NOT USE
+- controller-side web search is allowed while building `01-controller-answer-packet.json`
+- verifier1 must directly open controller-cited URLs before accepting the related claims
+
+Session continuation rule:
+- Once an answer-first tutoring session is open for a problem, copied classroom transcript blocks continue that same problem by default.
+- Expected continuation format is repeated speaker / timestamp / message blocks such as:
+  - `DeniseEvangelina`
+  - `0:00:16`
+  - `hello i keep getting kicked because of my wifi`
+  - `Joao B (Tutor)`
+  - `0:00:30`
+  - `No problem at all`
+- Parse the latest student-authored line and latest tutor-authored line from the copied classroom text.
+- Treat transcript-form continuation as student-session input.
+- Treat plain normal-language operator text as control input, not as a student classroom line.
+- If the operator ends or redirects the session in normal language, stop continuation handling and follow the control instruction.
+
